<h2>Portfolio-Data</h2>

	<h3>Web Site Overview</h3> 
	<p>This mobile site is a proof-of-concept, playground, etc. for accessing the <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/finance/" target="foo">Google Finance API</a>. After user authentication, the page flow is as follows:
	<ol>
		<li>Home page lists the user's Google Finance portfolios</li>
		<li>Next page lists the selected portfolio's positions</li>
		<li>Final page lists the selected position's transactions</li>
	</ol>	
	</p> 
	<h3>Technology</h3> 
	<p>
	<ol>
		<li>Framework: <a href="http://jquerymobile.com/" target="foo">jQuery Mobile</a> (1.1.0 RC 1)</li>
		<li>Authentication: Uses the Google <a href="http://code.google.com/apis/accounts/docs/AuthSub.html" target="foo">AuthSub</a> authorization process</li>
		<li>Stock Quotes: Uses <a href="http://developer.yahoo.com/yql/" target="foo">Yahoo! Query Language (YQL)</a> to get the last trade information on the positions</li>
	</ol>
	</p> 
			

</body>
</html>